  "prompt": "What is Deliveroo business model?",
  "response": "Deliveroo's business model is centered around food delivery services, with several key components:\n\n1. Platform Model\n- Online marketplace connecting restaurants, customers, and delivery riders\n- Acts as an intermediary between food providers and consumers\n\n2. Revenue Streams\n- Commission fees from restaurants (typically 20-30% of order value)\n- Delivery fees charged to customers\n- Subscription service (Deliveroo Plus/Deliveroo Unlimited)\n\n3. Key Value Propositions\n- Convenient food delivery from various restaurants\n- Wide restaurant selection\n- Real-time tracking of orders\n- Quick and efficient delivery service\n\n4. Operational Model\n- Uses independent contractor delivery riders\n- Technology-driven platform with mobile app and website\n- Advanced logistics and routing algorithms\n\n5. Technology Infrastructure\n- Mobile application\n- Sophisticated mapping and routing systems\n- Machine learning for demand prediction\n- Customer and restaurant management tools\n\n6. Target Markets\n- Urban areas with high population density\n- Young, tech-savvy consumers\n- Restaurants seeking expanded delivery capabilities\n\n7. Additional Services\n- Cloud kitchens (Deliveroo Editions)\n- Corporate meal services\n- Catering options\n\nThis multi-sided platform model allows Deliveroo to generate revenue while providing value to restaurants, customers, and delivery partners.",
